 This correction was done to correct for a bias introduced by possible undersamp
ling of the light curves, which would generate a lower estimate of the amplitude.
 The correction procedure attempts to bring the amplitude estimate as close
 as possible to what it would be if the object was observed at a 
\begin_inset Formula $60^{\circ}$
\end_inset

